Fellow software engineers/hackers/devs/code gardeners, do you keep a notebook (digital or plain dead-tree version) to record things you learn?  Since my days assembling glassware and synthesizing various chemicals in the organic chemistry lab, Iâ€™ve found keeping notes to be an indispensable tool at getting better and remembering important lessons learned. One of my professors recommended writing down, after every lab sessions, what had been accomplished and what needed to be done next time. When lab sessions are few and far apart (weekly instead of daily), it is easy to forget the details (for example, the mistakes that were made during weighing of chemicals ). A good quick summary helps with this!  When I first started working for a software company, I was overwhelmed.
